Residents in Kigumo, Murang&rsquo;a county, are afraid of venturing out at night and fear for the safety of schoolchildren returning home in the evening after an animal, believed to be a leopard, killed 10 goats in one week.Residents of Kiriti, Gatuya-ini and Mutunguru villages told the Star on Saturday they have been forced to keep their goats in their houses at night, as they do not want to lose more animals.Farmers have been unable to got to their farms early and boda boda riders rarely operate at night for their safety.